news.title: Residential real estate to see 10-12% annual sales growth through FY27: Crisil
news.para: India's residential real estate is set for steady growth, projecting a 10-12% annual increase in sales value, fueled by rising demand for premium and luxury housing. Sales volumes are expected to rise 5-7%, with average prices appreciating moderately.

news.title: GCCs account for 42% of India’s office leasing in FY25: Report
news.para: GCCs leased 31.8 million sq. ft. of office space during the fiscal year, marking a 24% year-on-year growth. While the number of GCC transactions dropped 4% to 305 deals, the average leased area per transaction increased, reflecting a trend towards larger office spaces and long-term expansion commitments.

news.title: Aatish Kapadia and wife buy apartment worth ₹15.31 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Aatish Kapadia, noted actor-director, and his wife Alison Kapadia, have invested ₹15.31 crore in a Goregaon apartment within Oberoi Realty's Elysian project. The spacious 3,030 sq ft apartment comes with three parking spots.

news.title: Arkade Developers acquires Filmistan for ₹183 crore
news.para: Arkade Developers, a Mumbai-based company, is set to acquire Filmistan for ₹182.95 crore, paving the way for a four-acre residential project in Goregaon West. The high-end development, planned for launch in 2026, will feature two 50-storey towers with luxury apartments and penthouses, with an expected gross development value of ₹3,000 crore.

news.title: Capital raised by real estate firms triples in FY25: Equirus Capital
news.para: Large-cap players led the fundraising, clocking Rs 3,93,898 million, followed by REITs at Rs 3,12,012 million. Small-cap and mid-cap firms raised Rs 66,938 million and Rs 52,626 million, respectively.

news.title: Indian cement sector set for 6–7% growth in FY26: ICRA
news.para: India's cement industry is set for robust growth in FY2026, with volumes expected to rise by 6-7%, reaching 480-485 million metric tonnes, driven by housing and infrastructure demand. Capacity additions are projected to increase significantly.

news.title: ED raids suspended HMDA official; ₹250 crore assets, realtor links under probe
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) conducted searches at multiple locations linked to suspended HMDA official Shiva Balakrishna, following an investigation into disproportionate assets. The ACB had arrested Balakrishna and his brother in January, revealing assets worth ₹250 crore.

news.title: One in two homes sold in H1 2025 cost over ₹1 crore
news.para: Premium housing dominates India's residential market in H1 2025, accounting for 49% of sales, while affordable housing declines. NCR leads premium sales at 81%, contrasting with an 18% drop in sub-₹50 lakh sales. Despite overall sales dipping 2%, prices rise, especially in NCR and Bengaluru, highlighting a shift towards higher-value properties.

news.title: Not just the wealthy: This innovation lets everyone build wealth from real estate
news.para: The truth is, despite being one of the most proven and desirable investment avenues, real estate in India is structurally inaccessible to most people.This isn’t due to a lack of intent, working professionals across the country aspire to own a property.

news.title: India’s office space demand hits record 48.9 million sq ft in H1 2025
news.para: The unprecedented surge in demand was driven by strong leasing activity in Bengaluru, NCR, and Pune, with Global Capability Centres (GCCs) leading the absorption. GCCs alone contributed 39% of total leasing, followed by third-party IT services (22%), flex operators (21%), and India-facing businesses (18%).

news.title: NCR records 7.2 million sq ft office leasing in H1 2025
news.para: NCR's real estate market soared in the first half of 2025, according to Knight Frank. Office leasing hit a record 7.2 million sq ft, driven by GCCs and domestic firms, with Gurugram leading. Ultra-luxury home sales surged by 2,550%, contrasting with a slight dip in overall residential sales.

news.title: Office market sees 40% surge in net leasing across top seven cities in H1 2025: Anarock
news.para: India's commercial real estate market saw a strong recovery in the first half of 2025. Office leasing in top cities increased significantly. Bengaluru led in absorption, while Pune showed the highest growth. Kolkata was the only city with a decline. New office completions also rose. Vacancy rates slightly decreased, but Hyderabad had the highest rate.

news.title: Onward Workspaces to invest ₹20 crore to add 1.2 lakh sq ft space in Delhi-NCR
news.para: Onward Workspaces is set to expand its footprint in Delhi-NCR with a ₹20 crore investment, adding 1.2 lakh sq ft of workspace. The expansion includes five new centers across Gurugram, Delhi, and Noida.

news.title: Domestic investments in Indian real estate surge 53% to $1.4 billion in H1 2025
news.para: India's real estate sector attracted USD 3 billion in institutional investments in H1 2025, with domestic investors contributing nearly half. While overall inflows declined 15% year-on-year, a 53% surge in domestic capital provided a buffer amid a slowdown in foreign investments.

news.title: BPTP to invest ₹3,000 crore in residential project on Dwarka Expressway
news.para: BPTP has introduced GAIA Residences, a housing project along the Dwarka Expressway. The company plans to invest ₹3,000 crore in this venture. The project is expected to generate revenue of ₹6,500 crore.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body starts land acquisition for Harnandipuram
news.para: GDA vice chairperson Atul Vats told TOI, "Land acquisition for any project can be tricky, and for its Harnandipuram township project, GDA needs to acquire 336 hectares from five villages."

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government issues guidelines for land pooling scheme-II, retains LPS-I norms
news.para: The government has already conducted grama sabhas in Tadikonda and Pedakurapadu constituencies to implement LPS-II and has set the groundwork for the formal launch of the scheme.

news.title: Nashik civic body to set up urban design cell to enhance city planning
news.para: It will focus on various aspects of urban development such as mapping infrastructure, promoting walkability and developing plans for making better places in the city.

news.title: Pune civic body starts disconnecting water connections to dilapidated wadas
news.para: Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) has identified 37 such properties for the action and sought assistance from police in the compulsory evacuation of the residents. Letters have also been sent to Maharashtra State Electricity Distribution Co. Ltd (MSEDCL) regarding connections to such wadas, a senior PMC official said.
